- The integer result is the minimum number of steps required to spell all characters in the keyword.
- The string parameter `ring` and `key` consist of only lowercase English letters.
- The length of the string parameters `ring` and `key` is between 1 and 100.
- The character `key[i]` must be aligned at the "12:00" direction by rotating the `ring` clockwise or anticlockwise.
- Each rotation of the ring by one place counts as one step.
- Pressing the center button after aligning the character `key[i]` at the "12:00" direction also counts as one step.
- After pressing the center button, the next character in the key is spelled.
- The key can always be spelled by rotating the ring.